title: Bug 121170 - getColumnLabel from IMetaData returns different results before/after data extraction
OB: When calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction, it does not return user recognizable strings. Instead, it returns some non-descriptive labels or placeholders.
EB: IMetaData.getColumnLabel() should return user recognizable strings that accurately describe the columns or data being extracted.
SR:
To reproduce the issue: 
1. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before extracting any data. 
2. Compare the labels returned with the expected user recognizable strings.
